main event: R. M. Caughlin observed 10 jet-shaped objects with green and white colors climbing from approximately 3000 ft to 20,000 ft on August 22, 1955.
interesting points: Initial evaluation indicated the objects were 'very bright stars', Three RAF jets were scrambled for interception but found no airborne sighting, Observation continued for an extended period, The reported colors included green and white, Object's altitude change was well documented.
witness description: R. M. Caughlin, a truck driver for the City of Grand Rapids
